A group known as Delta Monitoring Group (DMG), has lauded Delta State Governor Ifeanyi Okowa and members of Delta State executive council for their exploits in road construction across the State. Speaking with newsmen in Effurrun, the State coordinator of Delta Monitoring Group DMG, Comrade Otomewo Stephen said the Okowa-led administration had demonstrated a unique commitment to the massive development of Delta State mostly in the area of quality road construction and rehabilitation in his quest to give a huge sense of belonging and make life more meaningful to all Deltans. Otomewo also commended the members of Delta State Executive Council (Exco), for their huge support in ensuring that the stronger Delta Agenda of Governor Okowa is realised. EXPOSED - HOW LAGOS DOCTOR DISCOVERED MAJOR REASONS WHY MOST WIVES NOW HEAVILY CHEATS ON THEIR HUSBANDS AND THE PERMANENT SECRET TO SEXUALLY SATISFYING THEIR WIVES. DON'T BE A VICTIM! Otomewo said the recent approval of 13 roads during the (Exco), meeting on Tuesday 22/12/2020. shows that the Exco members who are drawn from the 25LGA are sensitive to the needs of their people in the area of quality road construction and rehabilitation. Speaking further, Comrade Otomewo Stephen also used the medium to commend the Hon. Commissioner for works Delta State. Chief James Augoye, describing Augoye as a square peg in a square hole and his impact in the works ministry is there for all to see. COVID-19: Nearly 9.5m Doses Of Vaccines Distributed, 1 Million Administered – CDC BPE Denies Diversion Of N14bn PHCN Sales Proceeds He remarked further: “Augoye is a reputable personality who has brought his wealth of knowledge and experience to bear in contributing immensely to the development of Delta State. The State coordinator of Delta Monitoring Group who is also the National Chairman of Okpe Development Front seized the opportunity to wish all Deltans compliment of the season and advised all citizens of Delta State to stay safe even as they 